496
00:42:20,940 --> 00:42:24,370
- Okay. 
 - No, that's not it...

497
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:29,340
I plan on trying to talk to my husband again...

498
00:42:29,340 --> 00:42:33,800
Hey, it's pretty easy to divorce a guy who's obviously horrible.

499
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:37,400
It's harder to divorce a guy only slightly bad.

500
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:42,840
I'm not getting mad at you or anything. The lawyer specializes in this; just try and meet him once.

501
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:45,000
I told him everything I know.

502
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:49,220
So have a seat, and ask whatever you're curious about.

503
00:42:49,220 --> 00:42:51,070
Lawyer.

504
00:43:16,530 --> 00:43:19,990
Has it been twenty years?

505
00:43:19,990 --> 00:43:23,530
You haven't changed one bit.

506
00:43:24,440 --> 00:43:26,940
You protected it.

507
00:43:26,940 --> 00:43:30,330
- What? 
 - Your face.

508
00:43:32,930 --> 00:43:37,140
George Orwell said "Once you turn fifty,

509
00:43:37,140 --> 00:43:41,890
one attains a face that speaks of one's value."

510
00:43:41,890 --> 00:43:46,930
But in reality, he died when he was forty-six.

511
00:43:48,020 --> 00:43:50,400
Even I don't want to see it.

512
00:43:51,160 --> 00:43:54,500
My face, which speaks of my worth or whatever.

513
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:59,230
Should I call it a relief that I might die before that?

514
00:43:59,230 --> 00:44:04,620
Even now, whenever I see myself in the mirror, I get surprised.

515
00:44:04,620 --> 00:44:09,540
Is this me? Is this my face?

516
00:44:09,540 --> 00:44:13,700
Come to think about it... I was always escaping.

517
00:44:13,700 --> 00:44:16,170
I couldn't protect anything.

518
00:44:16,170 --> 00:44:18,560
Since then...

519
00:44:19,500 --> 00:44:22,930
all I did was escape.

520
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,950
So...

521
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:12,650
Is he my boyfriend?

522
00:45:12,650 --> 00:45:14,330
- Yes. 
 - Yes, he is.

523
00:45:14,330 --> 00:45:16,700
We've kissed, but haven't slept together yet.

524
00:45:16,700 --> 00:45:18,740
You.. why are you telling me all that?

525
00:45:18,740 --> 00:45:21,910
Not... yet?

526
00:45:21,910 --> 00:45:23,480
When did Mom die?

527
00:45:23,480 --> 00:45:26,750
Why do you jump around without context in a conversation?

528
00:45:26,750 --> 00:45:27,740
Date.

529
00:45:27,740 --> 00:45:32,280
February 21st.

530
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:36,440
It's not far off.

531
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:38,740
I hope I die on that day.

532
00:45:38,740 --> 00:45:41,840
- Hey... what? 
 - It's nice to do it together on the same day.

533
00:45:41,840 --> 00:45:45,460
- Do what? 
 - Ancestral rites.

534
00:45:51,140 --> 00:45:53,310
My mother died in May.

535
00:45:53,310 --> 00:45:57,210
I will do it together for you on that day. Live a little longer.

536
00:45:57,210 --> 00:45:58,970
Spring is nice.

537
00:45:58,970 --> 00:46:02,260
I don't know your mother. Eating together is weird.

538
00:46:02,260 --> 00:46:04,430
- I don't give food. 
 - You should make offerings.

539
00:46:04,430 --> 00:46:06,410
- I only light candles. 
 - It has no sincerity.

540
00:46:06,410 --> 00:46:08,960
The atmosphere is fine. I light beautiful candles.

541
00:46:08,960 --> 00:46:11,100
Okay then.

542
00:46:11,710 --> 00:46:14,340
But still, one beer...?

543
00:46:14,340 --> 00:46:19,120
- No need. At least bottled water? 
 - Don't say such things.

544
00:46:19,120 --> 00:46:21,210
Why are you suddenly being like this?

545
00:46:23,070 --> 00:46:24,960
I am sorry.

546
00:46:24,960 --> 00:46:28,550
- What for? 
 - I keep getting this thought.

547
00:46:29,840 --> 00:46:34,190
Continuously, somehow

548
00:46:34,880 --> 00:46:40,150
if I would've lived together with your mom... you and your mom...

549
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:43,260
if you were together,

550
00:46:45,080 --> 00:46:48,170
maybe it wouldn't have turned out like this—

551
00:46:48,170 --> 00:46:51,290
If it were that way, I wouldn't have met Woo Cheon.

552
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:59,120
Come to think about it, everything was a chain reaction.

553
00:47:00,380 --> 00:47:06,310
If it was that way, then I wouldn't be here with him.

554
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:12,950
So, it's all right. We should just live on.

555
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:18,230
Though I lost one thing, I gained something else.

556
00:47:18,230 --> 00:47:21,340
- You should think like this to live comfortably. 
 - Don't act cool.

557
00:47:21,340 --> 00:47:24,570
- There's no reason you'd be all right. 
 - I am not trying to act cool.

558
00:47:24,570 --> 00:47:28,780
It just doesn't feel real to me.

559
00:47:30,210 --> 00:47:32,860
Because I don't know what dying is like.

560
00:47:35,970 --> 00:47:41,710
How that approaches you, or what happens...

561
00:47:41,710 --> 00:47:45,540
I don't know a thing, so I still feel fine.

562
00:47:52,700 --> 00:47:57,840
My father wanted to die along with me.

563
00:47:57,840 --> 00:47:59,960
Because living was hard.

564
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:05,800
He wanted to take me and my mom, but he died alone.

565
00:48:05,800 --> 00:48:11,830
But you abandoned your kid to live alone like this.

566
00:48:14,740 --> 00:48:18,450
On the wall of In Sook's house, there was a photo of Venice.

567
00:48:18,450 --> 00:48:21,540
I had asked her, why is it Venice?

568
00:48:21,540 --> 00:48:26,110
When I asked that, she said that her father called it Heaven.

569
00:48:26,110 --> 00:48:28,800
Stop it.

570
00:48:28,800 --> 00:48:31,250
That's why I want to go there.

571
00:48:35,480 --> 00:48:38,480

572
00:48:38,480 --> 00:48:40,520

573
00:48:40,520 --> 00:48:42,170
They say around this time is nice.

574
00:48:42,170 --> 00:48:44,970
- How can I go to this place? 
 - By plane.

575
00:48:44,970 --> 00:48:48,790
No. Why did you buy this? It's not even a penny or two.

576
00:48:48,790 --> 00:48:52,360
I just bought it. I will go there.

577
00:48:52,360 --> 00:48:56,780
- With you, together, I will go there somehow. So— 
 - Stop kidding.

578
00:48:56,780 --> 00:49:00,710
If you are like this, how would I feel?

579
00:49:01,300 --> 00:49:03,600
Let's go to Venice.

580
00:49:04,150 --> 00:49:07,610
- I don't have a ticket for you. 
 - I will buy it.

581
00:49:08,650 --> 00:49:13,320
I also want to go, with you. So...

582
00:49:23,410 --> 00:49:25,330
Why women other than Pyo In Sook?

583
00:49:25,330 --> 00:49:28,540
No. No, no.

584
00:49:29,050 --> 00:49:31,650
It doesn't match with Pyo In Sook's DNA.

585
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:36,150
I am saying it's not Pyo In Sook.

586
00:49:36,150 --> 00:49:38,980
- Earlier the components that were detected on the golf club— 
 - Sun cream.

587
00:49:38,980 --> 00:49:41,070
It was stuck on the head of the golf club.

588
00:49:41,070 --> 00:49:44,630
- I know, I know. 
  - You know, right?

589
00:49:44,630 --> 00:49:49,780
 Let me pass by.

590
00:49:56,550 --> 00:49:58,810

591
00:49:58,810 --> 00:50:01,480

592
00:50:04,640 --> 00:50:07,150
Yes, I had gone on the visiting day.

593
00:50:07,150 --> 00:50:11,110
Can I ask you what conversation you had?

594
00:50:11,110 --> 00:50:15,990
It was a general visit. That I was sorry

595
00:50:15,990 --> 00:50:18,980
for not taking care of her and having her live at the hospice.

596
00:50:21,720 --> 00:50:25,310
- It seems like you like golf. 
  - Yes.

597
00:50:26,200 --> 00:50:28,840
I thought I left that there that day.

598
00:50:28,840 --> 00:50:32,830
It was there, like that, when I came back home.

599
00:50:32,830 --> 00:50:37,320
By any chance, did you bring the golf club to the hospice that day?

600
00:50:39,610 --> 00:50:45,410
That... Is my wife related to the murder case somehow?

601
00:50:45,410 --> 00:50:47,210
It is her.

602
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:50,350
- She also tried to kill me. 
 - Mom!

603
00:50:50,350 --> 00:50:52,070
At night, she entered my room and—

604
00:50:52,070 --> 00:50:54,860
tried to choke me.

605
00:50:55,630 --> 00:50:58,180
Why is it my Se Yeon?

606
00:50:58,180 --> 00:51:02,540
Why? Why are you all like this to her?

607
00:51:10,300 --> 00:51:12,810
I heard you asked the lawyer to take up the case.

608
00:51:12,810 --> 00:51:14,540
Yes.

609
00:51:14,540 --> 00:51:18,460
But did you already know each other?

610
00:51:18,460 --> 00:51:19,680
Yes.

611
00:51:19,680 --> 00:51:22,430
She's a senior from college.

612
00:51:22,430 --> 00:51:26,220
Hey, it must be fate. That's good.

613
00:51:57,400 --> 00:51:59,640
Mom.

614
00:52:01,240 --> 00:52:04,120
Where was I at this time?

615
00:52:05,150 --> 00:52:07,880
You were not there.

616
00:52:08,530 --> 00:52:10,130
What?

617
00:52:10,130 --> 00:52:13,460
Ten years ago

618
00:52:14,760 --> 00:52:19,770
- you were not in this world. 
 - Ahh.

619
00:52:21,240 --> 00:52:26,890
- Are you sad? 
 - No, why?

620
00:52:26,890 --> 00:52:29,150
It's like that.

621
00:52:29,150 --> 00:52:30,940
What?

622
00:52:31,560 --> 00:52:34,590
Dying is...

623
00:52:35,260 --> 00:52:38,210
like that.

624
00:52:39,840 --> 00:52:44,170
Just not being here...

625
00:52:44,170 --> 00:52:47,170
It's like going back

626
00:52:48,050 --> 00:52:50,900
to before you were born.

627
00:52:53,660 --> 00:52:56,400
It's not sad, right?

628
00:52:58,250 --> 00:53:02,080
Yes. It's not sad, Mom.

629
00:54:55,210 --> 00:54:57,440
It's weird...

630
00:54:57,440 --> 00:54:59,370
What?

631
00:55:02,620 --> 00:55:08,280
I remember that scene.

632
00:55:10,470 --> 00:55:14,260
 The first time I went to the sea,

633
00:55:15,010 --> 00:55:17,660
 I lost the ring my mom gave me

634
00:55:17,660 --> 00:55:21,770
 on the beach.

635
00:55:21,770 --> 00:55:25,890
 I searched through the sand for a long time.

636
00:55:25,890 --> 00:55:30,670
 I looked and looked.

637
00:55:32,570 --> 00:55:36,720
 I don't know how much time passed like that.

638
00:55:37,810 --> 00:55:41,810
 Around the time I forgot what I was even looking for,

639
00:55:41,810 --> 00:55:45,270
 I stopped and looked up.

640
00:55:46,670 --> 00:55:52,540
 The view in front of me was so beautiful.

641
00:55:55,160 --> 00:55:57,120
 It was as if

642
00:55:58,720 --> 00:56:02,170
 my life was that way.

643
00:56:27,350 --> 00:56:33,890

644
00:56:33,890 --> 00:56:38,060

645
00:57:06,070 --> 00:57:08,280
Take care.

646
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:12,810
Don't be sick anymore.

647
00:58:49,180 --> 00:58:51,160
 Hello.

648
00:58:52,130 --> 00:58:54,120
 And.

649
00:58:55,900 --> 00:58:57,820
 Bye.

650
00:58:58,660 --> 00:59:01,080
Either way,

651
00:59:04,130 --> 00:59:07,410
greetings are not something you can prepare for.

652
00:59:10,800 --> 00:59:19,400

653
00:59:19,400 --> 00:59:22,860

654
00:59:22,860 --> 00:59:26,370
 Though my mom passed away, I think it was a happy ending.

655
00:59:26,370 --> 00:59:28,350
 In the video, someone suspected to be Ha's daughter...

656
00:59:28,350 --> 00:59:30,760
 What about the wrongs my dad did to me?

657
00:59:30,760 --> 00:59:33,530
 I have evidence that they ordered the murder.

658
00:59:33,530 --> 00:59:35,840
 Do you want to team with them and die, or team up with me and live?

659
00:59:35,840 --> 00:59:38,640
 That woman is dying! Why do you have to do this?

660
00:59:38,640 --> 00:59:41,250
 In Sook will never turn herself in because I won't let her do so.

661
00:59:41,250 --> 00:59:45,080
 - Let's get married. 
 - I'm scared. I feel like I just started becoming happy...

662
00:59:45,080 --> 00:59:49,290
 Let's do it. The most intense thing that a man and a woman can do.
